# Needs Engine quality loop

When the user asks to iterate on prescription quality, run the autonomous loop in [docs/NEEDS_ENGINE_QUALITY_LOOP.md](../../docs/NEEDS_ENGINE_QUALITY_LOOP.md).

## Mandatory workflow

1. Run unit tests listed in the loop doc.
2. Run `node scripts/evaluate-prescription-quality.mjs` with `DATABASE_URL` from `backend/.env.local`.
3. Fix failures in priority order (restore → progression gates → box avoid → fill → split2 progressions).
4. Re-run until evaluator exits 0.
5. Commit and push without asking when tests + evaluator pass.
6. Append result to [docs/NEEDS_ENGINE_QUALITY_LOOP.log](../../docs/NEEDS_ENGINE_QUALITY_LOOP.log).
7. Stop only when two consecutive PASS log lines exist; set Status to COMPLETE in the loop doc.

Do not ask the user to re-prescribe manually unless verifying production UI after deploy.
